Make that 3 1/2 forks. This is great, and tomorrow I'm making it with Toasted Garlic Rice with Fresh Herbs and Lime from this site. I wouldn't marinate these very long--shrimp just don't require much marinating. If you want to up the flavor factor, use the marinade instead as a sort of "dressing" that you toss the shrimp in after grilling. This is a trick I've used many times with grilled meats that have disappointed me flavor-wise even after marinating for hours. Bon appetit!

